Store Token in Jenkins Credentials
Step 1 — Add token to Jenkins credentials

Go to Jenkins → Manage Jenkins → Credentials → Global → Add Credentials
Set:

Kind: Secret text
Secret: <your sonarqube token>
ID: sonar-token
Description: SonarQube project token


Click Save

Step 2 — Remove token from sonar-project.properties

Step 3 — Inject token via Jenkins pipeline

stage('SonarQube Analysis') {
    steps {
        withSonarQubeEnv('sonarqube') {          // injects SONAR_HOST_URL automatically
            withCredentials([string(credentialsId: 'sonar-token', variable: 'SONAR_TOKEN')]) {
                sh '''
                    sonar-scanner \
                      -Dsonar.token=${SONAR_TOKEN}
                '''
            }
        }
    }
}
